    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The primary reasons for the overrepresentation of certain racial groups in the prison system in the US are rooted in systemic racism and biases. For instance, African Americans are disproportionately represented due to the war on drugs, which has led to harsher sentencing and mandatory minimums, resulting in more Black people being incarcerated for non-violent offenses. Similarly, Hispanics are overrepresented due to immigration policies and the enforcement of stricter border control, leading to increased detention and deportation rates. Additionally, Native Americans are overrepresented due to historical trauma, poverty, and lack of access to quality education and job opportunities.",
